articles.title: If You Have These Models Of iPhone, iOS 16 Won't Be Supported
articles.content:
Apple, Inc.'s (NASDAQ: AAPL) annual  Worldwide Developers Conference is almost around the corner. The highlight of the software-focused event is the release of the latest versions of the company's operating system, named iOS 16 for iPhones and iPadOS 16 for iPads.
Bloomberg columnist Mark Gurman is preparing Apple users to expect "fairly significant" enhancements across the board with the new OS. An update to notification and new health-tracking features could be in the offing, although an "end-to-end redesign" to iOS interface is ...
